# WendyOS: network-online.target provider policy (NetworkManager mode).
#
# With NetworkManager as the active network manager, NetworkManager-wait-online
# already provides network-online.target. systemd-networkd-wait-online would
# also be pulled in and *fail*: by default it waits for every networkd-managed
# link to come online, including the Tegra camera-over-ethernet NICs (mgbe*)
# that normally have no carrier. It times out, exits 1, and shows up red in
# `systemctl --failed` even though the target itself is reached fine.
#
# Keep it from being auto-enabled. Numbered low (15-) so it wins over the
# systemd vendor preset that would otherwise enable it.
disable systemd-networkd-wait-online.service
